{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"nonmystic-archetypic-gibbon","description":"## Why\n\nThe 2026-07-08 principal-architect audit (Reliability finding #3) found that three documented reconciler safety mechanisms are implemented, tested, and **never called in production** — the safety they promise is illusory, and the current epic's children do not cover them:\n\n1. **Create→label crash window double-creates Jira issues.** `dispatch_one.py:241-256` runs `create_issue` → then adds the `rebar-id:` label the JQL dedup keys on → then binds in memory only; bindings persist only at end of pass (`reconcile.py:1068`). A hard crash between create and label leaves an orphan issue invisible to dedup; the re-run creates a duplicate.\n2. **The write-ahead/recovery protocol is dead code — and miswired.** `binding_store.py:6-16` documents pending→confirm; `bind_pending` has zero production callers, and `run_differs.py:267` passes the applier module (which has no `search_issues`) as the client to `recover_pending_bindings`, so real recovery would `AttributeError` into a fail-open swallow (`run_differs.py:268-274`).\n3. **Crashed pass deadlocks reconciliation forever.** Lease `steal()` is implemented and tested (`_ref_lock.py:470-533`) but the held-ref path unconditionally exits 3 (`__main__.py:534-539`); after a SIGKILL the remote `refs/reconciler/lock` persists until an operator hand-deletes it.\n4. **All three retry layers are inert.** The REST helper re-raises every `HTTPError` (`acli_rest.py:61-63`); `_call_with_backoff` (`acli_subprocess.py:236-292`) has zero production call sites; the applier's `_call_with_retry` only retries `JiraAPIError`, which nothing in the client layer raises (`dispatch_one.py:100-144`). Sibling C4 (lambswool-shaded-eider) fixes only the bulk-path 429 parity — it does not revive these layers.\n\n## What\n\nWire each mechanism into its intended call site, smallest-change-first:\n- Translate `HTTPError` → `JiraAPIError` at the client boundary (`acli_rest.py`) — the one seam that revives `_call_with_retry` and enables backoff on 429/5xx; ensure non-idempotent writes (create/comment) are only retried when a dedup key (rebar-id label / comment marker) already exists, per the write-safety invariant at `acli.py:262-264`.\n- Call `bind_pending` + persist the binding store **before** `create_issue`, confirm after label attach; fix `recover_pending_bindings` to receive a real client with `search_issues`, and make recovery failures loud (alert, nonzero manifest tally) instead of fail-open.\n- In `__main__.py`'s held-lock path, invoke `steal()` when the lease is expired (fence semantics already implemented); keep exit 3 for a live, unexpired holder.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: `acli_rest.py`, `acli_subprocess.py`, `dispatch_one.py`, `run_differs.py`, `binding_store.py` callers, `__main__.py` lock path, plus tests. Out: bulk-path 429 parity (C4 owns it), inbound status mapping (owned by the audit-remediation epic), any refactor of the retry helpers themselves.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `HTTPError` from the REST path is translated to `JiraAPIError` at the client boundary; `_call_with_retry` demonstrably retries a simulated 429 with Retry-After honored, and a simulated 500 with jittered backoff\n- [ ] Non-idempotent writes are never blindly retried before their dedup key exists (test: timed-out create is not re-sent without a prior rebar-id search)\n- [ ] `bind_pending` is written and the store persisted before `create_issue`; a crash injected between create and label leaves a pending record that the next pass recovers via a working `search_issues` client (no duplicate issue)\n- [ ] `recover_pending_bindings` receives a client object exposing `search_issues`; a recovery failure raises an alert and a nonzero manifest tally instead of a silent swallow\n- [ ] A pass encountering an expired lease steals it via `steal()` and proceeds; a live unexpired lease still exits 3 (both covered by tests)\n- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/scripts/bridge/ -q` green","id":"9622-17ce-daa6-4778","parent_id":"ace2-f784-4b19-4f22","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Wire the reconciler's dead safety machinery: bind_pending write-ahead, lease steal(), and retry-layer error translation"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783540957065767001,"uuid":"46210295-6050-45f9-b82d-626134e6dd76"}